        <h2 style="text-align:center;"> <u>Convex Optimization </u></h2>
        <p>In 2017 I took a class on <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Convex_optimization">Convex Optimization</a> with a wonderful professor, <a href="http://www.ece.rutgers.edu/~kdana/">Kristin Data</a> who specializes in computer vision.  Convex problems are "nice" problems because they are "simple", esentially they are problems that have exactly one minimum (or maximum) value.  Despite this simplicity, you can accomplish some extraordinary things: create models to maximize profits/income contrained to perceived risk in investments and budget restrictions, for example.</p>
        <p> The class was very challenging for me, but was worth it because of how often the topic comes up in different areas of study, and the assignments were outstanding.</p>

        <h3 style="text-align:center;"> Image Segmentation </h3> 
