        <h3 style="text-align:center;"> Final Project: Kernel SVM </h3>
        <p>As my final project in the class, I studied how to do image predition using <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Support_vector_machine">Support Vector Machines (SVMs)</a> using the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kernel_method">"kernel trick"</a>.  SVMs are basically algorithms that try to find a best fit "straight line" that seperates data.  Again, despite their simplicity, they can be very powerful, and are widely used to do amazing things. </p>
        <p>I think I might have gone a bit overboard with this project, but I had a lot of fun doing it, and was very pleased with presenting the idea of SVMs from the start, working through all the math (with colored equations!!), and putting together a good experiment to test things with.  You can read it for yourself <a href="../../documents/cvx_opt/cvx_opt_final_report.pdf">here</a>.</p>
    
